topic.title: Maximum Bandwidth

body.p: The maximum bandwidth used by the RI_RCP is independent of the number of channels used within an individual framer and is only dependent on how much overall bandwidth is used. For the calculations below, a maximum throughput of 600G was used for each framer stage.

The maximum bandwidth is however directly dependent on the worst case ODU frame period which is provided in the second table below for the various ODU clients. These values were selected for each stage to calculate the maximum bandwidth.
The RI_RCP has a worst case bandwidth of 3.1 Gbps which is much less than the 10 Gbps provided by the 10GE interface.

entry.p: TCM1 + TCM2 + TCM3 + TCM4 + TCM5 + TCM6 + PM
Preamble + SFD + DA + SA + EtherType + FCS + IPG
Ethernet Header + OH + APS_PCC + Status Byte + (ODU Frame OH * ODU Frames/PDU)
Worst case traffic type for given stage (one with the smallest ODU frame period)
Worst case ODU frame period for given stage (based on Worst Case Traffic)
Number of channels required for maximum 600G framer throughput
1/(ODU Period * ODU Frames/PDU) * (Ethernet Frame Size) * (bits per byte)
Stage 1 + Stage 2 +Stage 3a + Stage 3b + Stage 4 + Stage N
PPM offsets have very little effect and are not included in the above calculations.
